betterquesting:10.desc:8: You can grind down Iron and Coal and then blend the dust together to get Steel Blend.
By exploding TNT nearby Steel Ingots, you can obtain Compressed Iron Ingots (don't ask me how that works). (Disclaimer: We are not liable for the 10% loss that this process does)
The Air Compressor starts up the early stages of industrailization, utilizing the power of pressure to do mechanical work at paces faster.
This machine utilizes heat to melt down an object or to solidify an object.
By making a mortar, you can craft Grout by mashing Gravel, Clay and Dirt together to make Grout which will be needed for Seared Brick and then the Smeltery
By having this system, you can make Seared Brick at paces faster than the before method.

By pouring Silicon into the §mbeef cast§r Boule Cast, you can cast a Silicon Boule, which can be cut into plates and then to Silicon itself.
This machine uses heat and/or pressure to transform a solid or a solid and a fluid to another fluid.
Biomass is made by pressurizing and heating organic matter in a Thermopneumatic Processing Plant.
By distilling Biomass you can get 100mB of Crude Oil and 540mB of Water, you essentially have an infinite source of oil.
The Refinery uses heat to distill a fluid into multiple fluids, which will be essential for progression.
By hammering an Conductive Iron Ingot and two Steel Plates together, you can make 4 Basic Universal Cables which will be your primary way of transmitting power for a while.
By inscribing Diamond in an Inscriber, you get a Printed Engineering Circuit.
By inscribing Gold in an Inscriber, you get a Printed Logic Circuit.

By distilling Crude Oil in a Refinery, you can obtain the chronology of LPG, Gasoline, Diesel and Kerosene. LPG is essential in Plastic Production and the rest is used as fuel for the Gas Turbine Generator or distilled into LPG via the Thermopneumatic Processing Plant
The Gas Turbine Generator generates Power from burnable fluids (liquids and gases). With the Advanced Generators mod, the generator is extremely modular, fitting into any area.
By inscribing Silicon in an Inscriber, you get a Printed Silicon.

By casting Iron into Redstone, it turns into an Enriched Alloy, the first alloy used in the next chapter.
